	(text "Experiment not implemented: I want to see\nwhat happends if I drive the oscillator at\nsomething like 25V or more. This is a boost converter"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 227.838 149.86 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "39dfd407-1453-4b4c-9a09-fd17a33b86ec")
	)
	(text "This bias is used to provide an offset\nto the Q signal that otherwise saturates\nthe sampling integrator. \nThe input DC is provided by DAC1 and it needs\nto be amplified since 3.3V may not be enough."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 523.748 215.646 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "9f19560b-a225-4c47-97cc-f69baff8d857")
	)
	(text "When no target is present, both I and Q singals should be 0V. \nIn order to achive this (in this version of the circuit), the \nuser should act on the encoder in order to center the sampling \nwindow so that the I signal reaches 0, then it should act on the\npotentiometer that, through an offset, nulls the Q signal.\nOnce the DAC output will be implemented, a push of the encoder\nwill allow to switch between these two settings in order to \ndo it more easily.\n\nIn the future, the STM32 will read the ADC bias (2.7V as today) and\nit will automatically set both the sampling window and the Q offset\nso that they will be zero, implementing some sort of auto calibration.\nthe encoder will still be usefull to move the sampling window in otder\nto perform ground balancing."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 435.356 135.636 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "a1df4de3-4548-4363-82a2-e0498987b2ec")
	)
	(text "Simple comparators that extract a square wave from the TX signal.\nIt is mandatory to add a decoupling capacitor between the comparator\nand the TX singal for two reasons:\n\n1. The cross coupled oscillators has a DC component equal to Val/2\n2. It allows to precisely trigger at the zero crossing of the TX signal\n\nFuture versions will make use of the STM32 internal pullup."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 81.28 186.436 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "ab0bf276-794e-4780-8c3a-91ca10d0fa4f")
	)
	(text "The system provides two kinds of oscillators: a cross-coupled oscillator \nthat can be used for center plugged TX coils and a Collpits oscillator\nsuitable for \"single ended\" coils."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 89.916 29.464 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "b8f19c84-ab1f-4dc9-9ce2-216f5f7bb63b")
	)
	(text "This block implements the RX preamplifier and phase shifter\nto be fed to the demodulators. The RX preamplifier can be used\nfor differential coils, single ended coils or center plugged coils,\neven tho I think the gain should be reduced for the latter case."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 286.766 118.364 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "c8b8ee77-77b0-4bc3-9176-4322a162a3cc")
	)
	(text "This bias is used to provide a DC offset to the ADC\ninputs. Since all of the signals lowers when a \nmeaningfull target is detected, this offset is set\nto 2.7V, in order to allow a bigger dinamic for\ntarget that lower both I and Q signals."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 442.214 216.662 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "dd2b077f-c758-466a-adf9-a12c57fb3d01")
	)
	(text "Fine tune balancing circuits.\nNever tested, do not know if I\nwill ever implement them"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 211.836 115.57 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "deee7b38-d58c-4e77-9e5c-a68e02e4e0ea")
	)
	(text "Unimplemented: for now I am using the \nNUCLEO dev board to provide both 3.3V\nand 5V."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 367.538 162.814 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "e7d5ed35-4576-4afb-9c50-019a3eda5f3a")
	)
	(text "The I signal is actually the one that samples \nthe RX at 90°. This appened because the coil\nproduces, when no target is present, a small\nRX signal that is 90° shifted to the TX.\nFuture updates will see an update on the signal\nnames, but for now I prefer to leave all like this."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 513.08 83.566 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "ed7d93dd-ab9b-4a69-b6cd-e405ebf83afe")
	)
	(text "Inverting charge pump driven by two signals with dead time\ninsertion in order to dissipate as less power as possible.\nOutput voltage is about -6V"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 228.854 261.366 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "ede457a1-a07b-41b1-bbff-86be97014304")
	)
	(text "Note: do not drive this at +Vbatt\notherwise the 3.3V logic signals\nwill always be read as LOW!!!"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 410.464 57.912 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "f5d62f68-e995-411b-a6bd-9421175849a5")
	)
	(text "As mentioned above, the Q signal is actually\nthe one that samples the RX signal in phase.\nIt is a strong signal when no target is present,\nit lowers when a meaningfull target is present \nand rises when the target is ferrous.\nIn needs bias to be set to 0 when no target are present,\nso that the biggest output swing dinamic is achived."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 513.334 147.574 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "f987bbd8-2cc2-4f33-80e7-3ffc3cc24ea1")
	)
